sep.gaia.resources.wikipedia

Class WikipediaManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sep.gaia.resources.ResourceObservable<R>
      • sep.gaia.resources.DataResourceManager<WikipediaData>
        • sep.gaia.resources.wikipedia.WikipediaManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LoaderEventListener<WikipediaData>, StateObserver

    public class WikipediaManager
extends DataResourceManager<WikipediaData>
implements LoaderEventListener<WikipediaData>
    Management object to load wikipedia short descriptions from wikipedia. Instances of the class observe the current GLState and the instance of POIManager and react to a change of the state. This is important, because the PointOfInterest objects for which wikipedia articles exist are needed.
    Author:
    Michael Mitterer

    • Constructor Detail

      • WikipediaManager

        public WikipediaManager()
        The constructor creates a new wikipedia loader and a new temporary cache. All loaded WikipediaData objects are hold in this cache and are deleted, if it's full.

    • Method Detail

      • load

        public void load(WikipediaData dummy)
        Initiates a load procedure at the overgiven dummy object. A WikipediaLoaderWorker thread is created, which will load the data into the WikipediaData object and then call the EventLoaderListener when it has finished.
        Parameters:
        dummy - The WikipediaData dummy that has to be filled with the short description.
        See Also:
        WikipediaLoaderWorker
